---
import "../styles/global.css"
---

<poll-context-section>
    <h3 class="section-title">Why this question was used</h3>
    <p>
        This question is designed to measure two things. First, how many people are
        willing to participate in an online poll about an Enfield ballot issue.
        Second, how the responses compare to actual election results, specifically
        whether the mix of “yes” and “no” responses here reflects what we see on election day.
    </p>
    <p class="fine-print">
        Responses are completely anonymous, and there is no way to identify who submitted them.
        This test also does not prevent multiple submissions, so please limit your responses
        to one per registered voter.
    </p>
</poll-context-section>

<script>
    class PollContextSection extends HTMLElement {}

    customElements.define("poll-context-section", PollContextSection)
</script>